headline: 3 Consumer Stocks We Find Risky
summary: Most consumer discretionary businesses succeed or fail based on the broader economy. Lately, it seems like demand trends have worked in their favor as the industry has returned 12.3% over the past six months, outpacing S&P 500 by 1.9 percentage points.
